'''Greg Allen''' ( born 27 October 1947) was{{cn|date=April 2018}} an Australian [[rugby league]] footballer who played for the [[Cronulla-Sutherland Sharks]] in the [[New South Wales Rugby League]] competition. His position of choice was [[Rugby League positions#second row forwards|prop-forward]].
== Early career == Before signing on to the Cronulla-Sutherland club Allen was a strongly built sheep shearer hailing from the country town of Warren in north western New South Wales.
